<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-01-0643 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book provides a general and technical overview of AI, its software,hardware and applications. Explores this technology in a straightforwardmanner. It begins with the basic concepts of AI and builds on them, explainingnew concepts as they logically occur. Volume I deals with fundamentalsof AI. It introduces the basic concepts, explains what AI is and is not,reviews its markets, applications, commercial future, limitations andpitfalls. It describes the techniques for representing knowledge in expertsystems, reasoning with the knowledge, and building experts systems.It also explains the basic concepts and techniques of language understandingsystems and discusses the differences between natural language system.</TEXT></DOC>